## Proposed Solution — Seven-Day Breakdown

One sprint. One governed workflow. One named owner on the {{ company_name }} side. Each day has a defined output and a founder checkpoint.

| Day | Activity | Output |
|-----|----------|--------|
| **Day 1** | Kickoff session (45 min) + Source Passport signed | Confirmed scope, named workflow owner |
| **Day 2** | Data import + Data Quality (DQ) score across six dimensions | DQ baseline score + deduplication report |
| **Day 3** | Account scoring + Top 10 selection with explainable rubric | Ranked list with transparent criteria (fit, signal strength, governance risk) |
| **Day 4** | Bilingual draft generation (AR + EN) + governance review | Draft pack marked "draft only" — no send without approval |
| **Day 5** | Proof Pack assembly (14 sections) | Complete Proof Pack + computed proof score |
| **Day 6** | Handoff session (60 min) + retainer-readiness assessment | Full Proof Pack walkthrough + recommended next step |
| **Day 7** | Capital asset registration + case-safe summary | Reusable asset logged in Capital Ledger |

**Governance note:** Dealix does not execute any external action (send, publish, pay) without a recorded approval with your identity and timestamp.

